East Africa-focused mineral sands producer Base Resources has delivered a financially outstanding performance over the last three years, largely thanks to an optimisation project implemented at its Kenya-based Kwale operation which has seen the mine improve its production and recovery deliverables – quite significantly. Now, the company is looking to build its financial strength further, by investigating the potential to extend Kwale’s mine life and introducing a second producing asset into the stable by 2021, MD Tim Carstens told delegates at the Africa Down Under conference in Perth, Australia in August. Laura Cornish reports. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 10 2018. It will be published online on the 01st November 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy